The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Ministry advice for IHF
New Delhi: Union sports minister Vikram Verma held a meeting with Indian Hockey Federation (IHF) chief K.P.S. Gill on Wednesday, discussing matters including selection of players for premier tournaments like Olympics. Though Verma said after the hour-long meeting that the selection issue was not discussed, sources said the ministry did convey its stand that the IHF should have clear and transparent policies on matters like selection. (PTI)  Copyright 
